        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 5:48PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Ross, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Middletown, Fairfield, Forest Park, Sharonville, Monroe,
Blue Ash, Trenton, Springdale, Harrison, Mount Healthy, West Chester,
Ross, Seven Mile, Taylor Creek, Dry Ridge, Blue Jay, Dunlap,
Williamsdale, and Olde West Chester.

This includes the following Interstates...
I-74 in Ohio between mile markers 0 and 7, and near mile marker 9.
I-75 in Ohio between mile markers 15 and 27.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
